Package prng.generator

This package provides implementations of pseudo-random number generators.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    SeedSource
    Something that can provide seed bytes on demand to a PRNG.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BaseRandom
    Common NIST secure random number functionality.
    HashSpec
    Specification for a Hash based RNG
    IsaacRandom
    The ISAAC random number generator is a cryptographically secure generator inspired by the RC4 cipher.
    NistCipherRandom
    An implementation of the NIST Cipher-based Deterministic Random Number Generator as defined in SP800-90A.
    NistHashRandom
    An implementation of the NIST Hash-based Deterministic Random Number Generator as defined in SP800-90A.
    NistHashRandom.RandomSHA1
    Implementation built around SHA-1
    NistHashRandom.RandomSHA256
    Implementation built around SHA-256
    NistHashRandom.RandomSHA512
    Implementation built around SHA-512
    NistHmacRandom
    An implementation of the NIST HMAC-based Deterministic Random Number Generator as defined in SP800-90A.
    NistHmacRandom.RandomHmacSHA1
    Implementation built around SHA-1
    NistHmacRandom.RandomHmacSHA256
    Implementation built around SHA-256
    NistHmacRandom.RandomHmacSHA512
    Implementation built around SHA-512

Package prng.generator Description

This package provides implementations of pseudo-random number generators.
